      {
        "content": "\ud83c\udfad Welcome to the Formal Debate!\n\n\ud83d\udccb **Topic**: What is the nature of true knowledge?\n\n\ud83d\udc65 **Participants and Positions**:\n  \u2022 Socrates: Knowledge comes from questioning and self-examination\n  \u2022 Student: Knowledge comes from education and learning from others\n\n\ud83d\udcdc **Debate Format** (traditional):\n1. Main Arguments - Each participant makes 2 arguments\n\n\u2696\ufe0f **Rules**:\n  \u2022 Participants must argue for their assigned position\n\nLet us begin! Socrates, please present your opening statement.",
        "additional_kwargs": {},
        "response_metadata": {},
        "type": "human",
        "name": null,
        "id": "0316ce03-3e54-41de-978d-e851c0938169",
        "example": false
      },
      {
        "content": "Would you say that knowledge obtained from others is truly yours, or merely borrowed? How can one claim to possess knowledge without first questioning and examining it for oneself?",
